cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper deals with generating textures that can fool visual object tracking systems, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of robots and cameras, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of optimization strategies and adversarial losses indicates that it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with security and evasion of tracking systems, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
